He only touched down on Sunday but Manny Pacquiao wasted no time in starting his training on American soil with a run through the streets of Los Angeles.

The 36-year-old will meet Floyd Mayweather in Las Vegas on May 2 and he is in LA to complete the second part of his training camp at trainer Freddie Roach's Wild Card Gym.

Pacquiao posted a video of his run on his Instagram account on Monday as he looks to reach peak fitness for the mega-fight at the MGM Grand.

